<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,863]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,152,179]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Description</emphasis>
. Habitus as illustrated (
<figureCitation box="[612,698,152,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="46.[151,250,2006,2031]" captionTargetBox="[202,1421,436,1967]" captionTargetId="figure@46.[151,1435,417,1981]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 26. Hydrochus denarius n. sp., habitus and male genitalia of holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3587235" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3587235/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Size: 
<typeStatus box="[784,882,152,178]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">holotype</typeStatus>
(length/width, mm): body (length to elytral apices) 2.18 /0.88; head width 0.58; pronotum l/w 0.46/0.50; PA 0.50; PB 0.40; elytra 1.38 /0.88. Body size small (ca. 
<quantity box="[151,317,224,251]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.32" metricValueMax="2.46" metricValueMin="2.18" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="2.32" valueMax="2.46" valueMin="2.18">2.18–2.46 mm</quantity>
). Dorsum black, with very weak iridescence. Legs brown, with tibiofemoral joints darker. Punctation on elytra ca. 3– 
<date box="[324,352,261,287]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">4x</date>
that of pronotum. Elytra with odd numbered interstriae costate, costae ca. 0.5– 
<date box="[1244,1268,260,287]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">1x</date>
strial puncture diameter; 5 
<superScript attach="left" box="[278,291,295,309]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">th</superScript>
costate, usual area of callus not otherwise raised.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,863]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Pronotum slightly wider than long (as ca. 46/50), widest at anterior margin, markedly narrowed at base, sides very slightly sinuate, minutely denticulate, each denticle with a short seta; anterior margin weakly bisinuate, and with border of short, closely spaced setae; depressions deep and densely punctate, pits near anterior and posterior angles large and deep.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,863]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Elytra with spaces between strial punctures ca. 0.5x their diameter, to narrow ridges; apices widened and with submarginal groove having row of large, translucent punctures, another row of translucent punctures above groove.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,863]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Ventral characters: Mentum coarsely punctate, with shallow median fovea. Submentum with two very large, confluent or nearly confluent, foveae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,863]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[375,457,656,683]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="46.[151,250,2006,2031]" captionTargetBox="[202,1421,436,1967]" captionTargetId="figure@46.[151,1435,417,1981]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURE 26. Hydrochus denarius n. sp., habitus and male genitalia of holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3587235" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3587235/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) general characters: paramere tips pointed, straight in dorsal and ventral views, slightly arcuate in lateral view, extending well beyond aedeagal apex; basal piece long, in dorsal/ventral views oriented at an angle to parameres, very arcuate in lateral view; aedeagus simple, lanceolate shaped.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,863]" box="[199,1180,764,791]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Dorsal surface: pdmm very slightly overlapping aedeagus lateral margins; adbl lacking.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,863]" box="[199,1034,800,827]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Ventral surface: pvmm very slightly overlapping aedeagus lateral margins.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,836,836,863]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,863]" box="[199,836,836,863]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,837,863]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named in reference to the ten elytral costae.
</paragraph>
